Caitlin, Ciaran.","English (of Norman origin):","from the Middle English and Old French male or female personal name <i>Hilari(e)</i>, <i>Ilari(e)</i>, and <i>Elari(e)</i>, from Latin <i>Hilarius</i> and <i>Hilaria</i> ‘joyful’ (from Greek <i>hilaros</i>). The Latin name was chosen by many early Christians to express their joy and hope of salvation, and was borne by several saints, including a 4th-century bishop of Poitiers (died 368) noted for his vigorous resistance to the Arian heresy, and a 5th-century bishop of Arles. Largely due to veneration of Saint Hilarius of Poitiers, the name became popular in France in the forms <i>Hilari</i> and <i>Hilaire</i>, and was brought to England by the Norman conquerors. Although quite popular in France, it was only occasionally used in England, where it was confused with the name in 2 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellery","meanings":["variant of   Hillary  .","habitational name from Elleray in Windermere (Westmorland), probably from Old Norse <i>elri</i> ‘alder’ + <i>vrá</i> ‘nook’.","English:"]},{"name":"Gloor","meanings":["Swiss German: from a vernacular form of the Latin personal name <i>Hilarius</i> (see   Hillary  )."]},{"name":"Hillier","meanings":["English (Wiltshire and Surrey): occupational name for a roofer from Middle English <i>hil(l)ier</i>, <i>hul(li)er</i>, <i>hel(li)er</i> ‘roofer, slater, tiler’, agent nouns from the Middle English verb <i>hil(i)en</i>, <i>hel(i)an</i>, <i>hul(i)en</i> ‘to put a roof on; cover with a roof’.","French: from the personal name <i>Hillier</i>, a vernacular form of <i>Hilaire</i> (see   Hillary  )."]},{"name":"Alario","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Orazio, Carlo, Rocco, Salvatore, Vita, Vitina.","Italian: from a vernacular form of the personal name <i>Ilario</i>, from Latin <i>Hilarius</i> (see   Hillary  ).","Italian (Sicily): probably a status name from dialect <i>alariu</i> ‘herald’."]},{"name":"Glor","meanings":["German: from a vernacular form of the Latin personal name <i>Hilarius</i> (see   Hillary  )."]},{"name":"Hillery","meanings":["English: variant of   Hillary  . This name has long been established in Ireland (Clare)."]},{"name":"Hilaire","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Pierre, Antoine, Chantal, Edeline, Georges, Luc, Maryse, Mimose, Serge, Yolaine.","French and West Indian (mainly Haiti): from the personal name <i>Hilaire</i>, French form of   Hillary   1. This surname is most common in Haiti. Compare   Helaire  ."]},{"name":"Hilleary","meanings":["English (Essex): variant of   Hillary  . This form of the surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Allaire","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Andre, Lucien, Alphonse, Antoine, Armand, Emile, Michel, Pierre, Raoul, Raymonde, Rolande.","French: from the Old French personal name <i>Allaire</i>, a variant of <i>Hilaire</i> (see   Hillary  ). Compare   Dallaire  .","History: Jean and Charles Allaire, two brothers from the Poitou region of France, are recorded in Quebec City, QC, in 1662 and 1663, respectively, the years of their marriage. The descendants of one or another brother also bear altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Dallaire</i>, <i>Delair</i>, and <i>Delaire</i>. — Alexandre Allaire, a Huguenot refugee, brought the name from La Rochelle in France to New Rochelle, NY, in 1686, via the West Indies. He is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Hilario","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Julio, Alfredo, Luis, Abelardo, Arturo, Eduardo, Francisco, Juan, Mario, Pedro, Carlos, Cesar.  Portuguese Afonso, Joao.","Portuguese (<b>Hilário</b>) and Spanish: from a personal name ofthe same origin as   Hillary   1."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":25,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":34,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":69,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Hillary was born in 1190, in England. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Hillary. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"1190–":"1190–Surnud","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1220–1260":"1220–1260","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","Inglaterra":"England","Tolleshunt, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1190–":"1190–Kuollut","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1220–1260":"1220–1260","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","Inglaterra":"England","Tolleshunt, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1190–":"1190–Décédé","1190–Female":"1190–Décédée","1220–1260":"1220–1260","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1220":"1220","1260":"1260","Inglaterra":"Angleterre","